Key Match Events: Deniz Undav scored the first goal for Germany in the 30th minute.
Deniz Undav scored the second goal for Germany in the 36th minute.
Edin Dzeko scored a goal for Bosnia and Herzegovina in the 70th minute.
Post-Match Reflections: Deniz Undav was named Player of the Match for his brace.
Julian Nagelsmann's side held on for a narrow 2-1 victory despite having to withstand Bosnia's positive start.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Nikola Vasilj was the goalkeeper for Bosnia and Herzegovina.
Maximilian Mittelstadt provided the assist for Deniz Undav's second goal.
The match was held in Zenica, Bosnia and Herzegovina.
